title: Bulldogs Drop Conference Opener to Beavers
text:
Bulldogs Drop Conference Opener to Beavers 
By Norman Seawright III October 9, 2015 Updated Oct 9, 2015 at 10:49 PM CDT 
Bemidji, MN (NNCNOW.com) -- The University of Minnesota-Duluth (UMD) women's hockey team lost the first in a two-game series against Bemidji State University (BSU). 
The Bulldogs' Western Collegiate Hockey Association opener was a 0-2 shutout loss to the Beavers. Proctor native Reilly Fawcett scored the first goal for the Beavers, followed by Stephanie Anderson for her third of the season.
